Sars says a final tally of exactly how many people have submitted tax returns should become clear on Saturday. JOHANNESBURG - South African Revenue Service (Sars) says a final tally of exactly how many people have submitted tax returns should become clear on Saturday afternoon, with the deadline for non-provisional tax payers on Friday. Those using e-filing have until midnight to submit returns, with offices closing at 4pm for manual submissions. Spokesperson Sandile Memela says, e-filing will be active until 12-midnight. Memela says there has been a good response this year. Sars is very thankful to over 5.3 million taxpayers, who have come forward to submit their tax returns. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)